   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "## Step 0 - DataLoader\n",
    "\n",
    "Here we need collate_fn function.\n",
    "- The collate_fn() function starts by extracting all the English and Spanish texts from the given batch.\n",
    "- In the process, it also **adds an SoS token at the start of each Spanish text**, **as well as an EoS token at the end**.\n",
    "- It then tokenizes both the English and Spanish texts will use BPE tokenizer, which we will also make and train on this same dataset in \"Step 0 Tokenizers\"\n",
    "- Next, the input sequences and the attention masks are converted to tensors and wrapped in an NmtPair, which is named tuple\n",
    "  - Importantly, **the function drops the EoS token from the decoder inputs**, and **drops the SoS token from the decoder targets**.\n",
    "  - For example,\n",
    "    - the inputs may contain the token IDs for “\\<s> Me gusta el fútbol” but now \\</s>,\n",
    "    - while the targets may contain the token IDs for “Me gusta el fútbol \\</s>” but not \\<s>\n",
    "- Lastly, the function returns the inputs (i.e., the NmtPair) along with the targets. Then we just create the data loaders as usual.\n",
    "\n",
    "We will start with NmtPair Named Tuple, this is not necessary, but with the help of this errors can be avoided"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "mHVNKWXsqlK_"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import torch\n",
    "import torch.nn as nn"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "IE6yxicden3W"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from collections import namedtuple\n",
    "\n",
    "fields = [\"src_token_ids\", \"src_mask\", \"tgt_token_ids\", \"tgt_mask\"]\n",
    "class NmtPair(namedtuple(\"NmtPair\", fields)):\n",
    "  def to(self, device):\n",
    "    return NmtPair(self.src_token_ids.to(device), self.src_mask.to(device),\n",
    "                   self.tgt_token_ids.to(device), self.tgt_mask.to(device))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "hYnP6JKSn487"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def collate_fn(batch):\n",
    "  \"\"\"This is a collate function required by DataLoader\"\"\"\n",
    "  src_texts = [pair[\"source_text\"] for pair in batch]\n",
    "  tgt_texts = [f\"<s> {pair['target_text']} </s>\" for pair in batch]\n",
    "  src_encodings = tokenizer.encode_batch(src_texts)\n",
    "  tgt_encodings = tokenizer.encode_batch(tgt_texts)\n",
    "  src_token_ids = torch.tensor([enc.ids for enc in src_encodings])\n",
    "  tgt_token_ids = torch.tensor([enc.ids for enc in tgt_encodings])\n",
    "  src_mask = torch.tensor([enc.attention_mask for enc in src_encodings])\n",
    "  tgt_mask = torch.tensor([enc.attention_mask for enc in tgt_encodings])\n",
    "  # remove </s> from tgt\n",
    "  inputs = NmtPair(src_token_ids, src_mask,\n",
    "                   tgt_token_ids[:, :-1], tgt_mask[:, :-1])\n",
    "  labels = tgt_token_ids[:, 1:]\n",
    "  return inputs, labels"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "1pl6Ix67rARE"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from torch.utils.data import DataLoader\n",
    "\n",
    "# change this for the experiment\n",
    "batch_size=32\n",
    "\n",
    "nmt_train_loader = DataLoader(nmt_train_set, batch_size=batch_size,\n",
    "                              shuffle=True, collate_fn=collate_fn)\n",
    "nmt_valid_loader = DataLoader(nmt_valid_set, batch_size=batch_size,\n",
    "                              collate_fn=collate_fn)\n",
    "nmt_test_loader = DataLoader(nmt_original_test_set, batch_size=batch_size,\n",
    "                             collate_fn=collate_fn)"
   ]
  },
